1
00:00:00,520 --> 00:00:04,570
Eitoku Academy, a renowned school that children of the super-rich attend.

2
00:00:04,570 --> 00:00:06,650
It's a commoner cull!

3
00:00:06,650 --> 00:00:11,150
This is C5, the quintet that protects the school's dignity and order.

4
00:00:11,150 --> 00:00:12,560
And the leader is Haruto Kaguragi.

5
00:00:12,560 --> 00:00:15,670
There are no exceptions to commoner culls.

6
00:00:15,670 --> 00:00:18,970
My father's company went bankrupt and I became a hidden commoner.

7
00:00:18,970 --> 00:00:22,590
One day, Kaguragi found out about my secret.

8
00:00:24,300 --> 00:00:25,700
No way.

9
00:00:25,700 --> 00:00:29,290
But Haruto Kaguragi is actually a super weakling!

10
00:00:29,290 --> 00:00:32,280
Isn't there any way to keep her mouth shut?

11
00:00:32,280 --> 00:00:33,530
You have to make her yours.

12
00:00:33,530 --> 00:00:35,030
I'm generous.

13
00:00:35,030 --> 00:00:38,110
Unlike you narrow-minded commoners.

14
00:00:38,110 --> 00:00:39,940
Are rich people really that great?

15
00:00:39,940 --> 00:00:41,610
You're really hopeless.

16
00:00:41,610 --> 00:00:43,130
You like Oto-cchi, right?

17
00:00:43,130 --> 00:00:45,690
I said that there's no way I'd fall in love with a commoner!

18
00:00:45,690 --> 00:00:47,580
I have a fiancé!

19
00:00:47,580 --> 00:00:49,860
A fiancé?!

20
00:00:54,620 --> 00:00:58,020
Tenma... Hase?

21
00:00:59,050 --> 00:01:02,170
To think that they would meet under such circumstances!

22
00:01:02,170 --> 00:01:03,800
Tell Tenma Hase

23
00:01:03,800 --> 00:01:06,200
that he won't leave unscratched if he ever appears before me.

24
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:08,400
I knew it was you, Oto!

25
00:01:09,110 --> 00:01:13,100
- Oto?
- I saw you walking while passing by in the car.

26
00:01:13,100 --> 00:01:14,360
You are Kaguragi, right?

27
00:01:14,360 --> 00:01:18,270
I see... So you know about me?

28
00:01:18,270 --> 00:01:19,620
Of course.

29
00:01:19,620 --> 00:01:22,740
The C5 of Eitoku Academy is famous.

30
00:01:22,740 --> 00:01:24,310
So, what is it now?

31
00:01:24,310 --> 00:01:25,700
Both of you are acquaintances?

32
00:01:25,700 --> 00:01:27,480
Well...

33
00:01:27,480 --> 00:01:29,730
Rather than an acquaintance,

34
00:01:29,730 --> 00:01:31,560
she's my childhood friend.

35
00:01:31,560 --> 00:01:34,800
- And she's my...
- Master!

36
00:01:34,800 --> 00:01:36,340
Ah, Master!

37
00:01:36,340 --> 00:01:38,340
Kobayashi?

38
00:01:40,650 --> 00:01:42,970
I've found Master, who ran away from the mansion.

39
00:01:42,970 --> 00:01:46,350
Send for medical support immediately!

40
00:01:47,110 --> 00:01:49,650
One, two, let's go!

41
00:01:49,650 --> 00:01:53,030
- Idiots, let me go!
- I can understand why you are upset.

42
00:01:53,030 --> 00:01:55,690
Because you were hit by such a big slab of meat.

43
00:01:55,690 --> 00:01:57,470
I told you that I'm not upset!

44
00:01:57,470 --> 00:02:00,170
The clinical psychologist is also waiting for you.

45
00:02:00,170 --> 00:02:01,930
Don't you understand what I said?!

46
00:02:01,930 --> 00:02:03,280
Okay, let's go.

47
00:02:03,280 --> 00:02:07,440
Let me go! Let me go!

48
00:02:08,720 --> 00:02:11,550
Why was he being hit by a slab of meat?

49
00:02:11,550 --> 00:02:16,270
Don't worry about it. You don't have to know.

50
00:02:17,550 --> 00:02:19,090
I see.

51
00:02:19,090 --> 00:02:21,220
It's late now. Let me send you home.

52
00:02:21,220 --> 00:02:22,600
Okay.

53
00:02:25,210 --> 00:02:28,470
I told you! I don't need any treatment whatsoever!

54
00:02:28,470 --> 00:02:30,210
I'm sorry.

55
00:02:30,210 --> 00:02:32,130
Can you give me a minute?

56
00:02:32,130 --> 00:02:33,440
Kobayashi!

57
00:02:33,440 --> 00:02:35,490
My master, you need to be more careful.

58
00:02:35,490 --> 00:02:37,060
Isn't your back injured?

59
00:02:37,060 --> 00:02:40,250
I recovered as soon as I heard about your situation.

60
00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:41,770
What the heck?!

61
00:02:41,770 --> 00:02:43,150
Excuse me.

62
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:46,630
I'm not forgiving you for what you did to Konno,

63
00:02:46,630 --> 00:02:49,120
but thank you for saving me.

64
00:02:55,040 --> 00:02:57,730
What's the matter?

65
00:02:57,730 --> 00:02:59,920
My chest...

66
00:03:00,440 --> 00:03:05,610
Arrange for a heart surgeon and CT scan at the mansion!

67
00:03:07,340 --> 00:03:09,140
Thank you for sending me home.

68
00:03:09,140 --> 00:03:10,970
See you next Sunday.

69
00:03:10,970 --> 00:03:12,250
See you.

70
00:03:12,250 --> 00:03:13,380
Goodnight.

71
00:03:13,380 --> 00:03:14,740
Goodnight.

72
00:03:23,710 --> 00:03:26,760
What's up with today?!

73
00:03:27,880 --> 00:03:29,750
Welcome back, Oto.

74
00:03:29,750 --> 00:03:31,720
I'm home.

75
00:03:40,290 --> 00:03:43,660
You sure are thirsty.

76
00:03:44,550 --> 00:03:46,550
You must have had a hard day at work.

77
00:03:46,550 --> 00:03:48,540
It's not due to work...

78
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:50,940
but I'm extremely tired.

79
00:03:50,940 --> 00:03:53,300
At a time like this, you need to be refreshed.

80
00:03:53,300 --> 00:03:56,260
It's easier said than done...

81
00:03:56,260 --> 00:03:57,640
What?

82
00:03:58,480 --> 00:03:59,570
It's arrived.

83
00:03:59,570 --> 00:04:03,950
The thing I'm looking forward to every month!

84
00:04:04,790 --> 00:04:07,930
I say, what are you doing?

85
00:04:07,930 --> 00:04:10,660
Look at this.

86
00:04:10,660 --> 00:04:13,660
Don't you think I look good?

87
00:04:20,150 --> 00:04:23,540
I also need a change of pace.

88
00:04:23,540 --> 00:04:25,420
Okay, I understand.

89
00:04:25,420 --> 00:04:28,570
Want to try it on, too?

90
00:04:28,570 --> 00:04:30,210
I'm tired now. Maybe next time.

91
00:04:30,210 --> 00:04:31,920
It'll just take a minute.

92
00:04:31,920 --> 00:04:33,180
Wait. I have a call coming in.

93
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:34,800
[Manager]

94
00:04:35,350 --> 00:04:39,310
Sorry that you've to come to work at the last minute.

95
00:04:39,310 --> 00:04:40,760
No problem.

96
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:45,040
I didn't know what to do! Maeno just quit suddenly.

97
00:04:46,330 --> 00:04:48,070
What?

98
00:04:48,070 --> 00:04:48,980
Stop it!

99
00:04:48,980 --> 00:04:50,500
He's going to move house.

100
00:04:50,500 --> 00:04:55,340
He said he won't get involved with people at work again. I don't get it at all!

101
00:04:56,680 --> 00:04:57,500
Don't tell me...

102
00:04:57,500 --> 00:05:00,010
[School Dismissal Notification]

103
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:04,420
There are no exceptions...

104
00:05:04,420 --> 00:05:06,080
to commoner... culls...

105
00:05:06,080 --> 00:05:08,750
You're really hopeless.

106
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,700
There are no exceptions.

107
00:05:26,760 --> 00:05:28,480
Konno? It's me, Oto.

108
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:30,840
I'm sorry about what happened yesterday.

109
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:32,610
About what?

110
00:05:32,610 --> 00:05:34,780
I made you feel really bad.

111
00:05:34,780 --> 00:05:36,840
No worries!

112
00:05:36,840 --> 00:05:39,640
I received so many things.

113
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:41,240
It's totally fine.

114
00:05:41,240 --> 00:05:45,020
I can save on a week of expenses on food!

115
00:05:45,020 --> 00:05:48,780
But that guy was so mean to you...

116
00:05:48,780 --> 00:05:50,530
You got carried away, didn't you?

117
00:05:50,530 --> 00:05:53,400
This place is worlds apart from the land of commoners.

118
00:05:53,400 --> 00:05:55,180
Do you mean Haruto-cchi?

119
00:05:55,180 --> 00:05:56,460
Haruto-cchi?

120
00:05:56,460 --> 00:05:58,610
It did surprise me a little.

121
00:05:58,610 --> 00:06:00,640
But he looks like a good kid.

122
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:04,150
Do you really think so?

123
00:06:04,150 --> 00:06:08,990
Yes, he went after you immediately yesterday.

124
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:14,220
What was he trying to do?

125
00:06:14,220 --> 00:06:18,200
C5 wouldn't want to be involved with a commoner...

126
00:06:18,200 --> 00:06:21,600
Haruto's acting strange lately.

127
00:06:21,600 --> 00:06:25,080
- Huh?
- Is it because of the girl who's threatening him?

128
00:06:25,080 --> 00:06:26,490
How do you know about it?

129
00:06:26,490 --> 00:06:28,970
Sugimaru told me when I asked him.

130
00:06:28,970 --> 00:06:32,260
What happened to Haruto? Tell me.

131
00:06:32,260 --> 00:06:33,860
Tell me!

132
00:06:33,860 --> 00:06:36,990
- That meathead!
- And so?

133
00:06:36,990 --> 00:06:40,040
Who is that girl exactly?

134
00:06:40,570 --> 00:06:42,090
Don't ask me. Go ask Haruto yourself.

135
00:06:42,090 --> 00:06:45,440
You know about my feelings, right?

136
00:06:46,310 --> 00:06:49,800
I don't care what happens to Eitoku Academy.

137
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:56,090
I came to this school and joined C5, all because of Haruto!

138
00:06:56,090 --> 00:06:58,940
- Calm down.
- Like I said...

139
00:06:58,940 --> 00:07:02,560
I won't give up until I find the girl who's causing pain to Haruto.

140
00:07:02,560 --> 00:07:05,500
Okay, I will go find out.

141
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:07,100
Make sure you do it.

142
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:08,790
If you don't...

143
00:07:20,620 --> 00:07:22,050
I feel a bit better now.

144
00:07:22,050 --> 00:07:24,490
I'm counting on you.

145
00:07:24,490 --> 00:07:27,250
Damn. What's wrong with everyone?

146
00:07:27,250 --> 00:07:29,860
How is it with that girl we talked about?

147
00:07:29,860 --> 00:07:32,150
Don't just keep quiet and tell us!

148
00:07:32,150 --> 00:07:35,580
Broken hearts make people stronger.

149
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:36,990
Haruto, she dumped you?

150
00:07:36,990 --> 00:07:38,710
Of course not!

151
00:07:38,710 --> 00:07:40,550
She's head over heels in love with me.

152
00:07:40,550 --> 00:07:43,550
In the first place, she was the one who looked up to me.

153
00:07:43,550 --> 00:07:47,340
She's just threatening me to hide her feelings.

154
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:49,690
Can I have a moment with you?

155
00:07:49,690 --> 00:07:53,990
Despite being a commoner, she said she's got a fiancé.

156
00:07:53,990 --> 00:07:56,420
And Tenma Hase suddenly appeared.

157
00:07:56,420 --> 00:07:58,410
What a mess it is.

158
00:07:58,410 --> 00:07:59,570
Hase knows her?

159
00:07:59,570 --> 00:08:03,350
Apparently, she's his childhood friend.

160
00:08:03,350 --> 00:08:05,350
Gosh, it's pissing me off.

161
00:08:05,350 --> 00:08:08,770
Since yesterday, I can't get her out of my mind.

162
00:08:08,770 --> 00:08:11,580
You don't have to fall for such a girl.

163
00:08:11,580 --> 00:08:13,580
Huh? Why do you say that?

164
00:08:13,580 --> 00:08:16,490
Then why are you so obsessed with her?

165
00:08:18,850 --> 00:08:22,280
Well... that's because I want to punish her!

166
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:23,830
What?

167
00:08:23,830 --> 00:08:26,190
I want her to regret that she threatened me.

168
00:08:26,190 --> 00:08:29,660
I'll make her fall madly in love with me and then dump her.

169
00:08:29,660 --> 00:08:32,850
But she's got a fiancé, right?

170
00:08:32,850 --> 00:08:35,150
It's just the fiancé of a commoner.

171
00:08:35,150 --> 00:08:38,960
Do you think I'll lose to such a guy?

172
00:08:38,960 --> 00:08:41,690
Don't cause so much trouble, okay?

173
00:08:41,690 --> 00:08:42,800
Airi will be fuming.

174
00:08:42,800 --> 00:08:44,620
Why are you mentioning Airi all of a sudden?

175
00:08:44,620 --> 00:08:46,620
- How insensitive can you get?
- Okay.

176
00:08:46,620 --> 00:08:50,260
So, what should I do next to make her fall for me?

177
00:08:50,260 --> 00:08:51,450
Hey, Oto.

178
00:08:51,450 --> 00:08:53,640
- Do you like pancakes?
- Yes.

179
00:08:53,640 --> 00:08:57,150
Then, you must definitely try the next-gen pancake.

180
00:08:57,150 --> 00:08:58,370
Next-gen?

181
00:08:58,370 --> 00:09:00,900
I've just sent you a message about it.

182
00:09:00,900 --> 00:09:02,850
It's a newly opened shop,

183
00:09:02,850 --> 00:09:04,410
and has become a hot topic.

184
00:09:04,410 --> 00:09:06,100
It looks delicious.

185
00:09:06,100 --> 00:09:09,210
Since you didn't go for the parfait, shall we go today?

186
00:09:10,460 --> 00:09:12,600
Sorry, I forgot my purse today.

187
00:09:12,600 --> 00:09:14,210
What...?!

188
00:09:14,210 --> 00:09:17,100
Hey, Oto. Are things okay with you?

189
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:20,960
- What?
- If you have any problems, just feel free to tell us.

190
00:09:21,470 --> 00:09:22,830
Okay.

191
00:09:26,990 --> 00:09:29,810
I can't tell them that I can't go because I have to work.

192
00:09:29,810 --> 00:09:33,360
I can't go on pretending anymore.

193
00:09:33,360 --> 00:09:35,850
Working after school today?

194
00:09:36,890 --> 00:09:39,430
Huh? What do you want with me?

195
00:09:39,430 --> 00:09:42,980
Don't you have anything to say to me?

196
00:09:42,980 --> 00:09:44,860
What should I say?

197
00:09:44,860 --> 00:09:48,170
About what happened at the convenience store yesterday.

198
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:51,970
Oh! So the reason why Maeno quit was...

199
00:09:51,970 --> 00:09:53,780
Yeah.

200
00:09:53,780 --> 00:09:55,290
Kobayashi.

201
00:09:55,290 --> 00:09:57,010
Yes, Master.

202
00:09:57,010 --> 00:10:01,050
Look up on that Maeno guy who works at the convenience store.

203
00:10:02,790 --> 00:10:06,310
What? Could it be that he wants me to thank him?

204
00:10:06,310 --> 00:10:09,670
Thank you for helping me...

205
00:10:09,670 --> 00:10:12,390
Actions speak louder than words.

206
00:10:12,390 --> 00:10:14,720
What do you want me to do?

207
00:10:14,720 --> 00:10:16,860
Were those just empty words?

208
00:10:16,860 --> 00:10:18,700
Okay, I get it.

209
00:10:18,700 --> 00:10:23,990
I can't afford something too expensive, but let me know what you want.

210
00:10:23,990 --> 00:10:25,620
Then...

211
00:10:26,810 --> 00:10:28,260
Pa...

212
00:10:28,260 --> 00:10:29,510
Pa...?

213
00:10:29,510 --> 00:10:30,570
Pan...

214
00:10:30,570 --> 00:10:31,480
Pan?

215
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:33,340
Pan...

216
00:10:33,340 --> 00:10:35,000
pan...

217
00:10:35,000 --> 00:10:36,940
Underpants?

218
00:10:38,540 --> 00:10:40,950
No, you idiot!

219
00:10:40,950 --> 00:10:42,880
It's pancake!

220
00:10:42,880 --> 00:10:44,070
Pancake?

221
00:10:44,070 --> 00:10:46,910
Don't you know about the next-gen pancakes?

222
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:50,470
If you come with me to eat them, I'll call it even.

223
00:10:50,470 --> 00:10:53,490
Oh! My friends were talking about it just now.

224
00:10:53,490 --> 00:10:55,670
I guess it's really popular.

225
00:10:55,670 --> 00:10:58,690
A man like me would know what's trending.

226
00:10:58,690 --> 00:11:01,660
Well, I can go with you.

227
00:11:01,660 --> 00:11:03,190
Really?

228
00:11:03,190 --> 00:11:08,170
It's kind of awkward for a guy to go to a pancake shop alone, after all.

229
00:11:08,170 --> 00:11:10,330
When should we go?

230
00:11:10,330 --> 00:11:15,190
How about this Sunday? My schedule is full for the next six months,

231
00:11:15,190 --> 00:11:17,740
but miraculously, I've nothing on this Sunday.

232
00:11:17,740 --> 00:11:19,590
Okay, no problem.

233
00:11:20,140 --> 00:11:22,630
Sorry, I can't make it this Sunday.

234
00:11:24,410 --> 00:11:27,330
I have an appointment that day...

235
00:11:27,330 --> 00:11:30,090
How about this Saturday?

236
00:11:30,090 --> 00:11:32,200
Again, miraculously,

237
00:11:32,200 --> 00:11:33,180
I'm free.

238
00:11:33,180 --> 00:11:35,650
Then, how about 1PM?

239
00:11:35,650 --> 00:11:40,080
I'll see you at the clock tower at Ebisu Garden Place. At 1PM.

240
00:11:40,080 --> 00:11:42,770
Okay, it's decided then.

241
00:11:46,990 --> 00:11:49,340
What a simpleton.

242
00:11:51,480 --> 00:11:55,560
This will do it. I'll have nothing to do with him after this.

243
00:12:17,240 --> 00:12:22,290
[Boys Over Flowers Season 2]

244
00:12:22,290 --> 00:12:25,730
[Episode 2]

245
00:12:26,160 --> 00:12:30,460
You are going for the pancake, right?

246
00:12:30,460 --> 00:12:32,090
Yes, do I look weird?

247
00:12:32,090 --> 00:12:35,260
It's better to be a bit more casual.

248
00:12:35,260 --> 00:12:37,190
Casual?

249
00:12:39,050 --> 00:12:41,610
What's casual?

250
00:12:43,850 --> 00:12:48,190
- Something like this?
- Pardon me, but I'm not into fashion.

251
00:12:49,430 --> 00:12:51,840
I don't know what to do!

252
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:56,010
Perhaps you can take reference from your lucky item in the zodiac forecast.

253
00:12:56,010 --> 00:12:59,050
- Kobayashi!
- My deepest apologies.

254
00:13:00,190 --> 00:13:01,510
You're a genius.

255
00:13:01,510 --> 00:13:02,950
Excuse me?

256
00:13:07,060 --> 00:13:10,510
Why this cowboy attire?

257
00:13:11,250 --> 00:13:13,270
I didn't have a choice.

258
00:13:13,270 --> 00:13:16,250
The zodiac forecast says so.

259
00:13:19,040 --> 00:13:23,620
You seriously believe in the Mars rock and these lucky items...

260
00:13:23,620 --> 00:13:25,290
Shut up.

261
00:13:25,290 --> 00:13:26,620
Let's just go.

262
00:13:26,620 --> 00:13:30,280
That's right. I'm sure there'll be a long queue.

263
00:13:37,890 --> 00:13:39,260
Oh no, it's closed.

264
00:13:39,260 --> 00:13:40,930
On a Saturday...

265
00:13:40,930 --> 00:13:44,310
What should we do? Is there another pancake shop nearby?

266
00:13:44,310 --> 00:13:47,460
Huh? Wait! You can't do that!

267
00:13:47,460 --> 00:13:50,290
Thank you for coming, my owner!

268
00:13:50,290 --> 00:13:52,830
O-Owner?!

269
00:13:52,830 --> 00:13:54,720
I bought the shop yesterday.

270
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:55,760
Huh?!

271
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:58,140
I won't queue for hours just to eat pancakes.

272
00:13:58,140 --> 00:14:01,390
I can't believe he bought it just like that!

273
00:14:02,200 --> 00:14:04,090
Come on, let's sit down.

274
00:14:04,090 --> 00:14:05,560
Yes.

275
00:14:17,830 --> 00:14:19,830
Yummy...

276
00:14:21,230 --> 00:14:22,790
Is that so?

277
00:14:30,230 --> 00:14:31,990
Aren't you going to eat?

278
00:14:32,560 --> 00:14:34,520
I don't like whipped cream.

279
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:37,290
But you wanted to come to this shop, right?

280
00:14:37,290 --> 00:14:39,560
Doesn't this mountain of cream appeal to you?

281
00:14:39,560 --> 00:14:42,390
Shut up and just eat.

282
00:14:43,700 --> 00:14:45,410
What?!

283
00:14:45,410 --> 00:14:46,800
Isn't this a bit strange?

284
00:14:46,800 --> 00:14:48,970
He can come here alone if he buys the whole shop.

285
00:14:48,970 --> 00:14:51,630
And if he wants to bring a girl along...

286
00:14:52,550 --> 00:14:54,500
he can just ask the girl in C5.

287
00:14:54,500 --> 00:14:57,430
Bring everything that's in the catalogue.

288
00:15:00,010 --> 00:15:01,570
Don't tell me...

289
00:15:01,570 --> 00:15:03,460
Sorry to keep you waiting.

290
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,040
Excuse me...

291
00:15:10,110 --> 00:15:12,390
What's up? You want another one?

292
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:14,050
No.

293
00:15:14,930 --> 00:15:16,870
What do you want with me?

294
00:15:16,870 --> 00:15:18,370
It's hot!

295
00:15:18,370 --> 00:15:19,990
Hot!

296
00:15:20,700 --> 00:15:23,790
Do you want to know anything from me? Is it about Tenma?

297
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:26,640
Huh? Why are you talking about Tenma Hase?

298
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:31,030
Did he find out about my engagement with Tenma?

299
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:35,320
Or is it about the Mars rock and those weird items you've been getting online?

300
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:37,210
Well... not exactly.

301
00:15:37,210 --> 00:15:40,290
Don't worry about that, because I won't tell anyone.

302
00:15:40,290 --> 00:15:43,190
So it's alright to just leave me alone.

303
00:15:43,190 --> 00:15:45,870
Fancy saying that when you're the one who threatened me.

304
00:15:45,870 --> 00:15:47,950
If it's due to that...

305
00:15:48,620 --> 00:15:50,280
please accept my apology.

306
00:15:51,140 --> 00:15:54,770
I just want to remain at Eitoku Academy.

307
00:15:54,770 --> 00:15:58,610
For some reason, I can't go to other schools.

308
00:16:00,430 --> 00:16:02,120
I'm surprised.

309
00:16:02,120 --> 00:16:03,420
What?

310
00:16:04,170 --> 00:16:07,400
Don't tell me that you have the same reason, too?

311
00:16:07,400 --> 00:16:09,020
Same reason?

312
00:16:09,020 --> 00:16:11,350
The reason why you want to be at Eitoku Academy.

313
00:16:12,290 --> 00:16:14,380
It's because of F4, right?

314
00:16:14,380 --> 00:16:16,340
- What?
- I knew it!

315
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:17,820
Do you also look up to them?

316
00:16:17,820 --> 00:16:19,750
Sorry, but...

317
00:16:19,750 --> 00:16:21,410
Come with me.

318
00:16:21,980 --> 00:16:22,850
Wait up!

319
00:16:22,850 --> 00:16:23,710
[Domyoji]

320
00:16:23,710 --> 00:16:26,410
What's this place?

321
00:16:26,410 --> 00:16:28,460
I always come here alone.

322
00:16:28,460 --> 00:16:30,750
But it's special today.

323
00:16:30,750 --> 00:16:32,170
I see.

324
00:16:32,700 --> 00:16:34,320
Look!

325
00:16:34,320 --> 00:16:36,650
It's the mansion of Domyoji!

326
00:16:37,920 --> 00:16:39,930
Do... myoji?

327
00:16:39,930 --> 00:16:43,180
I'm here today, all thanks to Domyoji.

328
00:16:43,180 --> 00:16:46,680
- I wanted to be like him, so I formed C5.
- Stop.

329
00:16:46,680 --> 00:16:49,010
Can I ask you a question?

330
00:16:49,010 --> 00:16:50,110
What?

331
00:16:50,110 --> 00:16:53,820
Who's that "Domyoji" you're talking about?

332
00:16:54,820 --> 00:16:59,670
- Huh?
- Like you mentioned, he's one of the F4 members, right?

333
00:16:59,670 --> 00:17:02,370
Hey, hey, no way!

334
00:17:02,370 --> 00:17:06,870
You're a student in Eitoku, but you don't know who Domyoji is? He's the leader of F4!

335
00:17:06,870 --> 00:17:10,660
During elementary school, I remember seeing F4, but I don't know them well.

336
00:17:10,660 --> 00:17:13,310
Return me the excitement that I felt 30 seconds ago!

337
00:17:13,310 --> 00:17:15,570
You were the one who got excited on your own.

338
00:17:15,570 --> 00:17:17,960
This is such a special place to me.

339
00:17:17,960 --> 00:17:22,630
Do you always come here alone to wait for your idol to appear?

340
00:17:22,630 --> 00:17:25,910
Of course not! I came here to reaffirm my resolution.

341
00:17:25,910 --> 00:17:28,340
- Resolution?
- Yes.

342
00:17:28,340 --> 00:17:31,530
Hey, you! Leave this place.

343
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:35,520
You are a disturbance to stand around here.

344
00:17:35,520 --> 00:17:37,140
I'm sorry.

345
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:40,330
Hey, granny! What are you doing here in this house?

346
00:17:40,330 --> 00:17:42,510
This is the famous...

347
00:17:42,510 --> 00:17:45,700
The mansion of Domyoji, right?

348
00:17:45,700 --> 00:17:49,830
I'm the head of the housemaids here.

349
00:17:49,830 --> 00:17:53,170
Yes, this is the mansion of Domyoji...

350
00:18:00,510 --> 00:18:02,080
I'm sorry for my impudence!

351
00:18:02,080 --> 00:18:03,310
Wait!

352
00:18:03,310 --> 00:18:07,070
I'm Haruto Kaguragi, a second year student at Eitoku Academy.

353
00:18:07,070 --> 00:18:09,650
I see, so you're a student at Eitoku Academy.

354
00:18:09,650 --> 00:18:13,800
I've been working hard everyday, to become someone like Domyoji.

355
00:18:13,800 --> 00:18:15,750
Okay, let's go.

356
00:18:15,750 --> 00:18:18,750
- Please excuse us.
- Since you're here...

357
00:18:19,350 --> 00:18:21,270
would you like to have some tea?

358
00:18:21,270 --> 00:18:22,730
- What?
- What?

359
00:18:23,620 --> 00:18:26,450
What do you think? Do I look good?

360
00:18:28,570 --> 00:18:30,620
You can take a look for yourself.

361
00:18:33,500 --> 00:18:35,520
Doesn't this look great?

362
00:18:35,520 --> 00:18:39,420
Okay, I'll set it as my wallpaper.

363
00:18:39,420 --> 00:18:41,790
Let me take a selfie up there!

364
00:18:41,790 --> 00:18:44,330
- What?
- You should take one, too!

365
00:18:44,330 --> 00:18:48,250
- Hang on!
- Damn... this is too good to be true!

366
00:18:48,250 --> 00:18:53,470
At this rate, the sun will set before we can have tea.

367
00:18:53,470 --> 00:18:55,220
I'm really sorry.

368
00:18:55,220 --> 00:18:58,460
Well, he may be a little weird,

369
00:18:58,460 --> 00:19:02,040
but he doesn't look like a bad person.

370
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:05,450
I think so, too.

371
00:19:07,010 --> 00:19:08,830
What are you doing?

372
00:19:08,830 --> 00:19:10,400
Isn't it obvious?

373
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:14,500
I'm trying to make all my body cells feel this space.

374
00:19:14,500 --> 00:19:17,610
I guess you really like Domyoji a lot.

375
00:19:17,610 --> 00:19:21,280
Words can't describe how I feel.

376
00:19:21,280 --> 00:19:25,020
Edogawa, I've made a promise to myself.

377
00:19:25,020 --> 00:19:28,770
I'll become a leader of Eitoku, and not bring shame to this noble place.

378
00:19:28,770 --> 00:19:34,120
I'll turn it back into a school that everyone can be proud of, just like when Domyoji was there.

379
00:19:34,120 --> 00:19:36,960
I will not lose to Momonozono Academy.

380
00:19:39,350 --> 00:19:40,890
I see.

381
00:19:40,890 --> 00:19:45,350
I like men who are passionate.

382
00:19:45,350 --> 00:19:48,790
My master was like that, too.

383
00:19:51,060 --> 00:19:53,170
Seriously?

384
00:19:59,120 --> 00:20:01,450
We're finally here.

385
00:20:01,450 --> 00:20:03,710
Let me quickly go prepare some tea.

386
00:20:03,710 --> 00:20:06,050
This is amazing.

387
00:20:09,290 --> 00:20:11,070
Excuse me...

388
00:20:11,070 --> 00:20:13,010
I shall take my leave.

389
00:20:13,010 --> 00:20:15,580
What are you saying? This is the chance of a lifetime!

390
00:20:15,580 --> 00:20:17,320
I'm sorry.

391
00:20:17,320 --> 00:20:21,580
But I don't deserve to be here.

392
00:20:21,580 --> 00:20:23,030
What?

393
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:27,730
The reason why I must remain at Eitoku Academy,

394
00:20:27,730 --> 00:20:30,980
is totally different from yours.

395
00:20:30,980 --> 00:20:32,010
What?

396
00:20:32,010 --> 00:20:33,770
I thought of keeping it a secret,

397
00:20:33,770 --> 00:20:39,370
but you've been so honest with me.

398
00:20:39,370 --> 00:20:41,390
I thought that it would be rude of me.

399
00:20:42,270 --> 00:20:43,970
Edogawa?

400
00:20:44,530 --> 00:20:48,880
There's a condition underlying my engagement.

401
00:20:50,120 --> 00:20:56,220
And that's to remain at Eitoku Academy till I turn 18 years old.

402
00:20:56,710 --> 00:20:59,620
If I do, I will get married to Tenma.

403
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:06,940
That's why I don't have such noble aspirations like you.

404
00:21:08,410 --> 00:21:10,330
She's my childhood friend.

405
00:21:10,330 --> 00:21:13,120
So, Hase and this girl...?

406
00:21:14,140 --> 00:21:15,860
Anyway...

407
00:21:17,630 --> 00:21:22,460
please don't chase me out of Eitoku Academy for at least a year.

408
00:21:22,460 --> 00:21:24,310
I beg of you.

409
00:21:24,310 --> 00:21:26,850
Huh? What's this?

410
00:21:26,850 --> 00:21:28,720
I can't say anything at all.

411
00:21:28,720 --> 00:21:32,010
She's going to marry Hase?!

412
00:21:34,550 --> 00:21:36,110
I'm sorry. Please excuse me.

413
00:21:36,110 --> 00:21:38,110
Wait. Don't go!

414
00:21:38,110 --> 00:21:39,410
Damn it.

415
00:21:39,410 --> 00:21:41,470
Say something!

416
00:21:41,470 --> 00:21:43,350
Edogawa!

417
00:21:46,550 --> 00:21:50,250
You're a loser.

418
00:21:51,030 --> 00:21:54,650
Are you trying to depend on your fiancé to escape from poverty?

419
00:21:54,650 --> 00:21:56,720
Don't you have any pride at all?

420
00:21:56,720 --> 00:21:59,370
Damn it, I can't stop.

421
00:21:59,370 --> 00:22:02,000
What a pitiful life you have.

422
00:22:02,000 --> 00:22:03,620
It's pathetic.

423
00:22:03,620 --> 00:22:07,240
I can't bring myself to look at her.

424
00:22:07,240 --> 00:22:09,650
I know that, even if you don't say so.

425
00:22:10,360 --> 00:22:12,600
I'm really pathetic.

426
00:22:14,960 --> 00:22:21,030
But my pathetic life has nothing to do with you, right?

427
00:22:31,200 --> 00:22:32,990
Damn it.

428
00:22:33,500 --> 00:22:34,550
My chest is hurting again...

429
00:22:34,550 --> 00:22:36,600
What are you doing?!

430
00:22:36,600 --> 00:22:37,520
Ouch!

431
00:22:37,520 --> 00:22:41,110
What are you doing? You should be going after her!

432
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:44,350
- What?
- Apologize and make up with her!

433
00:22:47,070 --> 00:22:48,620
Apologize?

434
00:22:48,620 --> 00:22:50,220
That would be strange.

435
00:22:50,220 --> 00:22:53,110
I bought that pancake place just for this day.

436
00:22:53,110 --> 00:22:55,240
For her.

437
00:22:57,940 --> 00:23:01,420
For... her?

438
00:23:01,420 --> 00:23:06,130
My pathetic life has nothing to do with you, right?

439
00:23:11,420 --> 00:23:12,970
What's happening?

440
00:23:15,510 --> 00:23:20,140
- Someone, help!
- What's this pain in my chest?

441
00:23:31,390 --> 00:23:34,120
Thank you for sending him back.

442
00:23:34,120 --> 00:23:35,510
No problem.

443
00:23:38,420 --> 00:23:40,140
Please take care.

444
00:23:40,140 --> 00:23:42,350
Thank you very much.

445
00:23:53,400 --> 00:23:55,460
You must be tired.

446
00:23:55,460 --> 00:23:58,210
Thank you.

447
00:23:58,210 --> 00:24:00,930
You need to study for the exams.

448
00:24:00,930 --> 00:24:03,410
You don't really have to meet Oto once every month.

449
00:24:03,410 --> 00:24:05,120
I will meet her.

450
00:24:05,940 --> 00:24:10,210
That's what my mother wants me to do before she passed away.

451
00:24:15,820 --> 00:24:17,860
Well, enjoy yourself then.

452
00:24:18,900 --> 00:24:20,370
Okay.

453
00:24:39,790 --> 00:24:43,840
Oto! You look so pretty.

454
00:24:44,410 --> 00:24:46,210
Thank you.

455
00:24:46,210 --> 00:24:47,690
That reminds me...

456
00:24:47,690 --> 00:24:51,920
of that party we were invited to in Dubai.

457
00:24:51,920 --> 00:24:53,480
That's right.

458
00:24:54,210 --> 00:24:56,010
Miyoko should be...

459
00:24:57,180 --> 00:25:00,150
feeling happy in heaven.

460
00:25:06,750 --> 00:25:11,670
Tenma's new mother is really a good person.

461
00:25:12,300 --> 00:25:17,250
Despite us ending up in this state, she still approves of the engagement.

462
00:25:19,150 --> 00:25:20,970
She's really kind.

463
00:25:24,220 --> 00:25:28,050
Go and have fun today.

464
00:25:28,050 --> 00:25:29,750
I will.

465
00:25:34,040 --> 00:25:37,370
I'm really happy to be able to meet Tenma.

466
00:25:37,370 --> 00:25:39,050
But...

467
00:25:39,650 --> 00:25:41,210
Oto.

468
00:25:42,500 --> 00:25:45,290
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

469
00:25:45,290 --> 00:25:47,850
- Shall we go?
- Okay.

470
00:25:50,300 --> 00:25:56,390
Behind this excitement, I couldn't help but feel a prickling pain in my heart.

471
00:25:57,120 --> 00:25:59,200
This will not do.

472
00:25:59,200 --> 00:26:06,810
The porridge for Master can only be made with eggs from Nagoya.

473
00:26:08,090 --> 00:26:10,040
Bring everything that's in the catalogue.

474
00:26:10,040 --> 00:26:12,140
Sure, no problem.

475
00:26:16,250 --> 00:26:17,760
This!

476
00:26:17,760 --> 00:26:19,150
I will have this.

477
00:26:19,150 --> 00:26:22,610
That item is really popular,

478
00:26:22,610 --> 00:26:24,670
and is already sold out.

479
00:26:24,670 --> 00:26:26,980
What?! Why didn't you save it for me?

480
00:26:26,980 --> 00:26:28,610
I'm really sorry.

481
00:26:28,610 --> 00:26:31,030
I'll make sure to complain to my father.

482
00:26:31,960 --> 00:26:34,220
That dress!

483
00:26:37,340 --> 00:26:39,520
That girl... I've seen her somewhere.

484
00:26:39,520 --> 00:26:42,350
Sorry to keep you waiting.

485
00:26:42,350 --> 00:26:44,430
Tenma Hase?

486
00:26:50,570 --> 00:26:52,410
Kobayashi.

487
00:26:52,980 --> 00:26:55,650
I said I have no appetite.

488
00:26:58,120 --> 00:27:00,620
How astounding.

489
00:27:00,620 --> 00:27:02,030
What?

490
00:27:04,080 --> 00:27:07,860
You can't even take care of your own health.

491
00:27:07,860 --> 00:27:09,620
I'm sorry.

492
00:27:15,090 --> 00:27:16,470
[Nobi-nobi Energy Drink]

493
00:27:34,930 --> 00:27:36,700
I'm disappointed in you.

494
00:27:36,700 --> 00:27:39,040
I only need...

495
00:27:39,900 --> 00:27:41,550
a perfect son.

496
00:28:17,620 --> 00:28:21,110
Kaito, you are here.

497
00:28:21,110 --> 00:28:23,550
Seeing the number of times you called, of course I'd be here.
[45 missed calls]

498
00:28:23,550 --> 00:28:28,670
I didn't expect Tenma Hase to be Edogawa's fiancé
.

499
00:28:28,670 --> 00:28:33,100
To make things worse, I think I've caught some commoner disease.

500
00:28:34,710 --> 00:28:38,290
There seems to be something wrong with me.

501
00:28:38,290 --> 00:28:42,780
Master hasn't eaten anything since yesterday,

502
00:28:42,780 --> 00:28:47,010
and he couldn't sleep, too. He's in great pain.

503
00:28:47,960 --> 00:28:50,160
When I close my eyes,

504
00:28:50,160 --> 00:28:53,410
I see that girl's face.

505
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:55,440
Kaito.

506
00:28:55,440 --> 00:28:58,380
You should replace me in C5,

507
00:28:58,380 --> 00:29:00,260
and become Eitoku's ー

508
00:29:00,260 --> 00:29:02,730
This is the worst!

509
00:29:02,730 --> 00:29:04,290
Yeah.

510
00:29:04,290 --> 00:29:06,440
You're right.

511
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:08,050
Haruto, don't you get it?

512
00:29:08,050 --> 00:29:12,710
The disease that you've caught... is love!

513
00:29:13,360 --> 00:29:14,710
Love?

514
00:29:14,710 --> 00:29:18,600
You're in love with Oto Edogawa.

515
00:29:23,100 --> 00:29:25,420
Really?

516
00:29:27,640 --> 00:29:29,260
N-No way!

517
00:29:29,260 --> 00:29:31,310
Then I should give you rice with red beans* instead.
[*A celebratory dish in Japan]

518
00:29:31,310 --> 00:29:32,370
No way, you idiot!

519
00:29:32,370 --> 00:29:35,340
Just acknowledge your own feelings already.

520
00:29:35,340 --> 00:29:36,670
No way!

521
00:29:36,670 --> 00:29:39,470
I have many other things to do.

522
00:29:39,470 --> 00:29:41,780
I don't have the time for girls!

523
00:29:41,780 --> 00:29:44,810
Then why did you go out with her on a pancake date?

524
00:29:44,810 --> 00:29:48,450
That's because... I want her to suffer!

525
00:29:48,450 --> 00:29:51,010
Kobayashi, please tell him what you think.

526
00:29:51,010 --> 00:29:55,530
What? You mean me?

527
00:29:55,530 --> 00:29:57,480
Kobayashi.

528
00:29:57,480 --> 00:29:59,840
This is not love, right?

529
00:29:59,840 --> 00:30:02,220
- Well...
- Kobayashi.

530
00:30:02,220 --> 00:30:04,480
I lost my appetite...

531
00:30:04,480 --> 00:30:06,220
not because of love, right?

532
00:30:06,220 --> 00:30:09,720
- Love, to me, is...
- Love is...

533
00:30:09,720 --> 00:30:14,360
It's when you realize that you're thinking about her,

534
00:30:14,360 --> 00:30:19,880
and at the most unexpected moment, especially when you're feeling down,

535
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:25,660
you want to see her badly, no matter what.

536
00:30:26,690 --> 00:30:29,210
That's love, to me.

537
00:30:31,070 --> 00:30:33,800
Okay! Then it's wrong!

538
00:30:36,960 --> 00:30:41,600
There's no way I'd fall in love with a hidden commoner!

539
00:30:41,600 --> 00:30:43,840
Mrs. Rie recommended this place.

540
00:30:43,840 --> 00:30:45,730
It's lovely here.

541
00:30:45,730 --> 00:30:49,610
I've ordered the set course, but do you want anything else?

542
00:30:51,510 --> 00:30:53,790
No, I'm fine.

543
00:30:58,870 --> 00:31:00,330
Ouch...

544
00:31:00,330 --> 00:31:04,030
I should have come in my usual broken shoes.

545
00:31:07,990 --> 00:31:10,460
Okay.

546
00:31:10,460 --> 00:31:13,830
It may look a little crude, but it's comfortable.

547
00:31:14,540 --> 00:31:16,710
Why don't you try it, too?

548
00:31:20,340 --> 00:31:23,210
See, it's more comfortable, right?

549
00:31:23,210 --> 00:31:24,650
Yes.

550
00:31:32,970 --> 00:31:36,510
Mr. Hase, I've prepared the VIP room for you.

551
00:31:36,510 --> 00:31:39,590
It will be more quiet if you dine there.

552
00:31:39,590 --> 00:31:40,760
I see.

553
00:31:40,760 --> 00:31:42,660
Please excuse me.

554
00:31:43,760 --> 00:31:47,090
It's better to put that family in the VIP room.

555
00:31:47,090 --> 00:31:52,050
- What?
- The mother and baby will feel more at ease in a private room.

556
00:31:52,050 --> 00:31:56,410
I've always liked Tenma for his personality.

557
00:31:56,890 --> 00:32:02,190
He helps those in trouble, and creates a pleasant ambience.

558
00:32:02,190 --> 00:32:06,130
Perhaps that's because he doesn't need to pretend.

559
00:32:06,130 --> 00:32:10,390
There is nothing fake about him. He's always honest.

560
00:32:11,550 --> 00:32:13,570
Do you feel hungry?

561
00:32:13,570 --> 00:32:14,970
Yes.

562
00:32:15,820 --> 00:32:20,340
This is roast beef made from A5-ranked Kobe beef.

563
00:32:20,340 --> 00:32:22,760
Please enjoy.

564
00:32:27,230 --> 00:32:28,900
Is something wrong?

565
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:34,110
No, it's been a long time since I had roast beef.

566
00:32:34,110 --> 00:32:35,440
I'm glad to hear that.

567
00:32:35,440 --> 00:32:37,660
- Let's eat then.
- Okay.

568
00:32:39,210 --> 00:32:41,410
How's school recently?

569
00:32:42,090 --> 00:32:43,370
I'm enjoying it.

570
00:32:43,370 --> 00:32:46,310
There're many good people in the new class.
[School Dismissal Notification]

571
00:32:46,310 --> 00:32:49,730
We always chat during our breaks.

572
00:32:49,730 --> 00:32:53,290
Not long ago, I also went to eat parfait with some friends.

573
00:32:53,290 --> 00:32:54,930
Today...

574
00:32:54,930 --> 00:32:56,480
I see.

575
00:32:56,480 --> 00:32:58,440
I'm different from Tenma.

576
00:32:58,440 --> 00:33:02,750
My life is becoming full of lies.

577
00:33:02,750 --> 00:33:08,480
I'm becoming a total opposite from the Tenma I like.

578
00:33:08,480 --> 00:33:12,270
Have you found out anything about the girl who threatened Haruto?

579
00:33:12,270 --> 00:33:14,800
The investigation is not easy.

580
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:18,180
If I find you lying, I'll make your life real difficult.

581
00:33:18,180 --> 00:33:19,320
- I'm serious.
- Ouch...

582
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:20,690
- Let go!
- Hey!

583
00:33:20,690 --> 00:33:22,510
We're in the middle of our meeting.

584
00:33:22,510 --> 00:33:24,740
I'm sorry.

585
00:33:24,740 --> 00:33:27,590
What's this information about Momonozono Academy?

586
00:33:27,590 --> 00:33:32,070
The Issa Girls have gathered information about Tenma Hase.

587
00:33:32,550 --> 00:33:33,910
I see...

588
00:33:33,910 --> 00:33:36,280
He's not a simple person.

589
00:33:36,280 --> 00:33:43,090
It seems that it was his idea to gather all the B-grade rich people into Momonozono Academy.

590
00:33:43,090 --> 00:33:44,180
B-grade?

591
00:33:44,180 --> 00:33:47,940
Their parents' careers succeed based on luck. They are the new rich people.

592
00:33:47,940 --> 00:33:51,160
That's why the enrolment rate is increasing.

593
00:33:51,160 --> 00:33:54,820
Moreover, the school embraces freedom and puts the students in top priority.

594
00:33:54,820 --> 00:33:58,150
That's why students go to Momonozono Academy, instead of our school.

595
00:33:58,150 --> 00:34:02,030
There are rumors that the school will be made into a theme park, so it's fun to be there.

596
00:34:02,030 --> 00:34:04,190
- Wow!
- Don't be affected by the rumors.

597
00:34:04,190 --> 00:34:06,210
We don't even know if it's true.

598
00:34:06,210 --> 00:34:08,910
In that case, we need to confirm it.

599
00:34:08,910 --> 00:34:11,010
[Momonozono Academy]

600
00:34:13,720 --> 00:34:16,190
Isn't this just a normal school?

601
00:34:25,320 --> 00:34:27,830
The school bell is performed live?

602
00:34:29,040 --> 00:34:30,700
Is this normal?

603
00:34:30,700 --> 00:34:33,750
- This is ordinary to me.
- Excuse me, excuse me!

604
00:34:39,730 --> 00:34:42,260
No way!

605
00:34:42,260 --> 00:34:44,370
A nail salon?

606
00:34:44,900 --> 00:34:47,480
And so, they call it the Great Wall of China.

607
00:34:47,480 --> 00:34:51,910
A virtual classroom?

608
00:34:51,910 --> 00:34:54,150
A golf practice room?

609
00:34:56,100 --> 00:34:58,390
A gym with trainers?

610
00:34:59,830 --> 00:35:01,940
What is this?

611
00:35:01,940 --> 00:35:05,770
Their club activities include skydiving?

612
00:35:07,260 --> 00:35:09,380
All these look ordinary to me.

613
00:35:09,380 --> 00:35:13,090
You need to accept reality, Haruto.

614
00:35:13,090 --> 00:35:15,190
[VR classroom facilities]
[Robot cleaning and security]

615
00:35:15,190 --> 00:35:19,360
Hase is the one who made everything come true.

616
00:35:19,360 --> 00:35:22,050
What's with this "100% Realization"?

617
00:35:22,050 --> 00:35:25,150
This guy sure makes things happen!

618
00:35:31,930 --> 00:35:33,170
I'm back.

619
00:35:33,170 --> 00:35:35,210
She just came home.

620
00:35:35,210 --> 00:35:36,700
I'll pass the phone to her.

621
00:35:36,700 --> 00:35:39,300
Oto, it's Mrs. Rie on the phone.

622
00:35:39,300 --> 00:35:41,780
Hello? This is Oto.

623
00:35:41,780 --> 00:35:44,770
Oto, how was it?

624
00:35:44,770 --> 00:35:46,640
Did you enjoy the date?

625
00:35:46,640 --> 00:35:48,210
Yes, I enjoyed it very much.

626
00:35:48,210 --> 00:35:50,010
Thank you for everything.

627
00:35:50,010 --> 00:35:52,660
You even prepared the dress and booked the restaurant.

628
00:35:52,660 --> 00:35:56,120
Don't worry about it. I'm glad to do it for you.

629
00:35:56,120 --> 00:36:00,640
But I still have the dresses you gave me previously,

630
00:36:00,640 --> 00:36:03,040
so you don't have to send one every month...

631
00:36:03,040 --> 00:36:04,970
Don't be bothered by it.

632
00:36:04,970 --> 00:36:08,350
It's the least I could do when you meet Tenma.

633
00:36:08,350 --> 00:36:13,260
- Pardon?
- You need to look compatible with the Hase family.

634
00:36:13,260 --> 00:36:14,550
I did all this...

635
00:36:14,550 --> 00:36:19,020
just to make Miyoko in heaven feel better.

636
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:21,510
I guess you're right.

637
00:36:21,510 --> 00:36:23,460
As for your friends in school,

638
00:36:23,460 --> 00:36:25,850
you need to choose them wisely.

639
00:36:25,850 --> 00:36:30,530
I think the son of the Kaguragi family is also in Eitoku Academy...

640
00:36:30,530 --> 00:36:34,470
Hello to the all students and staff of Momonozono Academy.

641
00:36:34,470 --> 00:36:37,090
I'm Tenma Hase, president of the student council.

642
00:36:37,090 --> 00:36:40,660
There's a condition underlying my engagement.

643
00:36:40,660 --> 00:36:44,580
And that's to remain at Eitoku Academy till I turn 18 years old.

644
00:36:44,580 --> 00:36:47,210
If I do, I will get married to Tenma.

645
00:36:47,210 --> 00:36:51,520
When I walk around the school campus lately, I can feel the cheerfulness.

646
00:36:51,520 --> 00:36:53,430
Desserts are always provided free.

647
00:36:53,430 --> 00:36:55,240
It makes me want to transfer to this school.

648
00:36:55,240 --> 00:36:56,810
What's so good about it?

649
00:36:56,810 --> 00:36:58,520
They're just trying to bribe the kids.

650
00:36:58,520 --> 00:37:01,450
But it's good to be able to do your nails anytime.

651
00:37:01,450 --> 00:37:03,750
You all shouldn't be influenced so easily!

652
00:37:03,750 --> 00:37:05,420
Keep your voice down.

653
00:37:05,420 --> 00:37:08,150
You need to be proud of Eitoku...

654
00:37:08,910 --> 00:37:11,140
Thank you for coming to our school.

655
00:37:11,140 --> 00:37:12,260
What?

656
00:37:12,260 --> 00:37:13,930
Last month, we starting using...

657
00:37:13,930 --> 00:37:16,210
Matching identity to the student database.

658
00:37:16,210 --> 00:37:18,410
Verifying data...

659
00:37:19,940 --> 00:37:23,060
Unable to identify status.

660
00:37:23,060 --> 00:37:25,050
This is annoying. Don't make a fuss here!

661
00:37:25,050 --> 00:37:26,610
Don't get angry with the robot.

662
00:37:26,610 --> 00:37:27,970
Let's go back.

663
00:37:32,720 --> 00:37:34,610
Kaguragi...

664
00:37:36,540 --> 00:37:38,920
You're Takuya Komatsubara of Class 2D, right?

665
00:37:38,920 --> 00:37:42,290
Congratulations on your transfer to Momonozono Academy.

666
00:37:42,290 --> 00:37:44,720
It's Kaguragi from Eitoku Academy.

667
00:37:44,720 --> 00:37:47,170
C5 is here!

668
00:37:48,720 --> 00:37:51,630
So, are we celebrities here?

669
00:37:51,630 --> 00:37:53,410
It's not something to feel happy about.

670
00:37:53,410 --> 00:37:54,980
Let's go.

671
00:37:58,260 --> 00:38:00,190
Seems like we have a problem here.

672
00:38:00,800 --> 00:38:04,190
You need permission to enter our school grounds.

673
00:38:05,650 --> 00:38:09,410
We'll do anything to keep the school safe.

674
00:38:09,410 --> 00:38:12,370
First, apologize for causing disturbance in the school.

675
00:38:12,370 --> 00:38:15,460
Apologize! Apologize!

676
00:38:18,220 --> 00:38:20,620
I will only say this once.

677
00:38:23,300 --> 00:38:25,980
Get out of the way, you hindrance.

678
00:38:29,170 --> 00:38:30,850
Stop it!

679
00:38:32,930 --> 00:38:35,000
They're my guests.

680
00:38:36,580 --> 00:38:39,200
I won't allow any rude behaviour.

681
00:38:53,250 --> 00:38:55,050
Tenma, I'll do it.

682
00:38:55,050 --> 00:38:56,580
It's okay.

683
00:38:58,180 --> 00:39:02,800
Kaguragi has been treating my fiancée well.

684
00:39:02,800 --> 00:39:04,440
Fiancée?

685
00:39:04,440 --> 00:39:06,250
I didn't do anything for her anyway.

686
00:39:06,250 --> 00:39:07,670
Sugar or milk for you?

687
00:39:07,670 --> 00:39:10,310
- Milk.
- Sugimaru, keep quiet.

688
00:39:10,310 --> 00:39:15,740
It's an honour for our school to have C5 here with us.

689
00:39:15,740 --> 00:39:21,560
I heard that you've inherited the will of the legendary F4 at Eitoku Academy.

690
00:39:21,560 --> 00:39:23,270
So what?

691
00:39:23,270 --> 00:39:26,270
Especially the leader, Domyoji...

692
00:39:26,270 --> 00:39:29,280
Stop beating around the bush. What do you want?

693
00:39:29,900 --> 00:39:33,110
Why did you help us?

694
00:39:33,110 --> 00:39:35,500
Haruto, stop it.

695
00:39:39,980 --> 00:39:42,100
What I want is...

696
00:39:44,700 --> 00:39:49,720
I hope we can use this opportunity to deepen the friendship between our schools.

697
00:39:55,420 --> 00:39:57,020
- I don't care about that.
- Haruto.

698
00:39:57,020 --> 00:39:59,630
You're the ones who started the fight.

699
00:39:59,630 --> 00:40:01,890
By secretly distributing flyers around.

700
00:40:01,890 --> 00:40:05,540
Eitoku Academy will prevail over all schools.

701
00:40:05,540 --> 00:40:09,850
I won't lose to you, for sure.

702
00:40:12,940 --> 00:40:14,680
Kaguragi.

703
00:40:15,500 --> 00:40:16,810
What?

704
00:40:18,630 --> 00:40:22,800
I'll find the students who distributed the flyers and give them a warning.

705
00:40:23,550 --> 00:40:25,640
I'm sorry about it.

706
00:40:39,230 --> 00:40:43,290
He's better than I expected. That Tenma Hase.

707
00:40:43,290 --> 00:40:44,700
He's got a leader's charisma.

708
00:40:44,700 --> 00:40:46,920
Stop talking about Hase.

709
00:40:46,920 --> 00:40:48,890
Kaito was also taken aback, right?

710
00:40:48,890 --> 00:40:50,880
That he's such a capable person.

711
00:40:50,880 --> 00:40:52,780
That's because...

712
00:40:52,780 --> 00:40:54,000
You're leaving?

713
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:55,690
Then I'm leaving, too.

714
00:40:56,440 --> 00:41:00,210
Hey, Sugimaru. Get out of my way.

715
00:41:00,210 --> 00:41:01,980
Just leave him alone.

716
00:41:01,980 --> 00:41:06,100
- What?
- He's just met with a great wall to overcome.

717
00:41:06,100 --> 00:41:07,660
Just like what Ichiro* said...
[*Ichiro Suzuki, a famous Japanese baseball player]

718
00:41:07,660 --> 00:41:12,260
"Obstacles only come to people who strive to overcome them."

719
00:41:12,260 --> 00:41:14,330
What a loser.

720
00:41:19,770 --> 00:41:23,810
Tenma's new mother is really a good person.

721
00:41:23,810 --> 00:41:27,780
Despite us ending up in this state, she still approves of the engagement.

722
00:41:27,780 --> 00:41:31,340
You need to look compatible with the Hase family.

723
00:41:31,340 --> 00:41:34,570
Are you trying to depend on your fiancé to escape from poverty?

724
00:41:34,570 --> 00:41:36,480
Don't you have any pride at all?

725
00:41:36,480 --> 00:41:38,360
What a pitiful life you have.

726
00:41:38,360 --> 00:41:40,400
It's pathetic.

727
00:41:48,990 --> 00:41:52,980
Excuse me. Are you okay?

728
00:41:54,790 --> 00:41:56,520
Kaguragi?

729
00:41:59,880 --> 00:42:01,500
Edogawa?

730
00:42:02,060 --> 00:42:07,080
Huh? Why am I here?

731
00:42:07,080 --> 00:42:08,820
Can I help you?

732
00:42:09,550 --> 00:42:11,630
When you're feeling down,

733
00:42:11,630 --> 00:42:16,370
you want to see her badly, no matter what.

734
00:42:16,370 --> 00:42:17,690
No!

735
00:42:17,690 --> 00:42:21,020
She's Tenma Hase's fiancée...

736
00:42:21,610 --> 00:42:24,430
Are you even listening?

737
00:42:34,920 --> 00:42:36,620
Can't I be here?

738
00:42:37,810 --> 00:42:39,210
What?

739
00:42:40,170 --> 00:42:42,750
Can't I be the one?

740
00:42:42,750 --> 00:42:44,210
Excuse me?

741
00:42:44,810 --> 00:42:46,990
What are you talking about?

742
00:42:47,640 --> 00:42:49,680
Nothing...

743
00:42:49,680 --> 00:42:52,400
Oh, it's Haruto-cchi! How have you been?

744
00:42:52,400 --> 00:42:54,280
What's wrong with him?

745
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:56,030
Kaguragi?

746
00:42:57,450 --> 00:42:59,120
My stomach...

747
00:43:00,710 --> 00:43:02,350
Does it hurt?

748
00:43:02,350 --> 00:43:04,650
I'm too hungry to move.

749
00:43:04,650 --> 00:43:07,900
- Huh?
- I haven't eaten anything for the past two days.

750
00:43:07,900 --> 00:43:10,510
Fasting? Are you slimming down to look better?

751
00:43:10,510 --> 00:43:13,990
I'd better call your home and ask someone to pick you up.

752
00:43:14,760 --> 00:43:16,650
No!

753
00:43:16,650 --> 00:43:18,870
I don't want to go home!

754
00:43:18,870 --> 00:43:23,190
Today... my father will be at home.

755
00:43:23,740 --> 00:43:25,690
Are you going through a rebellious period?

756
00:43:25,690 --> 00:43:28,330
Do you even know anything about my problems?

757
00:43:28,330 --> 00:43:30,670
This is really complicated.

758
00:43:30,670 --> 00:43:32,370
Don't bother about me.

759
00:43:32,370 --> 00:43:35,550
But it will be a problem if you collapse in front of the store.

760
00:43:35,550 --> 00:43:37,530
Don't tell me you're both still in a quarrel?

761
00:43:37,530 --> 00:43:39,140
We aren't friends in the first place.

762
00:43:39,140 --> 00:43:41,050
Wanna to come to my house?

763
00:43:41,050 --> 00:43:44,970
- Huh?
- Oto-cchi will soon finish her work, too. Right?

764
00:43:44,970 --> 00:43:46,210
What?

765
00:43:46,730 --> 00:43:50,780
Sorry that it's a mess, but make yourselves comfortable.

766
00:43:50,780 --> 00:43:52,810
Make myself comfortable?

767
00:43:52,810 --> 00:43:55,980
- In such a small and shabby ー
- Don't say it!

768
00:43:55,980 --> 00:43:57,830
And you should take off your shoes!

769
00:43:57,830 --> 00:44:00,310
Oto-cchi, why don't you make him something to eat?

770
00:44:00,310 --> 00:44:01,400
What? Me?

771
00:44:01,400 --> 00:44:04,810
Yeah, feel free to use whatever is in the fridge.

772
00:44:04,810 --> 00:44:07,370
But make sure to check the expiry dates first.

773
00:44:07,370 --> 00:44:09,940
You can cook?

774
00:44:09,940 --> 00:44:14,190
I'm different from people who have chefs and helpers at home.

775
00:44:14,190 --> 00:44:16,830
And I said... take off your shoes!

776
00:44:18,690 --> 00:44:21,830
You two can make yourselves at home.

777
00:44:21,830 --> 00:44:23,170
Wait, Konno?

778
00:44:23,170 --> 00:44:25,990
I'll go get some drinks. I only have Chu-Hi* in the house.
[*Chu-Hi: shochu mixed with soda]

779
00:44:25,990 --> 00:44:28,420
In the meantime, you both should make up.

780
00:44:28,420 --> 00:44:30,270
Wait ー

781
00:44:40,030 --> 00:44:43,790
Give me a break. Why are you leaving us alone?

782
00:44:43,790 --> 00:44:45,720
This is awkward.

783
00:44:50,440 --> 00:44:53,230
Don't expect it to be delicious.

784
00:44:56,210 --> 00:44:58,120
I'm hungry...

785
00:44:58,120 --> 00:44:59,410
Ouch!

786
00:44:59,410 --> 00:45:01,320
What am I doing here?

787
00:45:01,320 --> 00:45:05,450
Why am I cooking for someone who's been so harsh to me?

788
00:45:05,450 --> 00:45:06,820
Watch it!

789
00:45:06,820 --> 00:45:08,840
What do you want?

790
00:45:08,840 --> 00:45:13,300
Well, it's the first time I'm watching someone cook.

791
00:45:13,300 --> 00:45:16,770
I'm not cooking anything complicated...

792
00:45:19,680 --> 00:45:21,530
That's dirty!

793
00:45:21,530 --> 00:45:23,610
I'm going to wash it.

794
00:45:39,880 --> 00:45:41,800
Why aren't you adding everything at once?

795
00:45:41,800 --> 00:45:43,960
Because they cook at different timings.

796
00:45:43,960 --> 00:45:46,730
If I add everything together, they'll turn soggy.

797
00:45:50,990 --> 00:45:54,250
It's so difficult...

798
00:46:00,440 --> 00:46:02,290
This is amazing.

799
00:46:02,290 --> 00:46:04,380
Did you perform magic on them?

800
00:46:06,430 --> 00:46:08,690
What a weird fellow.

801
00:46:08,690 --> 00:46:09,930
Ignore this filth!

802
00:46:09,930 --> 00:46:11,920
He acts all high and mighty,

803
00:46:11,920 --> 00:46:13,100
but he's like a kid at times.

804
00:46:13,100 --> 00:46:13,990
This is too good to be true!

805
00:46:13,990 --> 00:46:15,520
And he blabbers nonsense all of a sudden.

806
00:46:15,520 --> 00:46:17,870
Can't I be the one?

807
00:46:18,470 --> 00:46:21,510
What did you want to say back there?

808
00:46:21,510 --> 00:46:24,950
- What?
- When you said "Can't I be the one?"...

809
00:46:26,930 --> 00:46:31,100
Well.. that is...

810
00:46:31,100 --> 00:46:32,800
What?

811
00:46:35,030 --> 00:46:36,730
What I want to say is...

812
00:46:37,620 --> 00:46:42,810
Can't I... be...

813
00:46:42,810 --> 00:46:45,500
I'm back! Have you made up with each other?

814
00:46:45,500 --> 00:46:49,340
I told you that there's nothing between us.

815
00:46:51,400 --> 00:46:55,450
Oto-cchi! These vegetables taste great!

816
00:46:55,450 --> 00:46:57,900
Haruto-cchi, you eat up, too.

817
00:46:57,900 --> 00:47:01,430
I've not eaten anything made by others before.

818
00:47:01,430 --> 00:47:02,580
It's fine. Open your mouth!

819
00:47:02,580 --> 00:47:04,740
Konno!

820
00:47:08,670 --> 00:47:10,310
I can't guarantee that he'll like the taste.

821
00:47:10,310 --> 00:47:11,790
Yummy!

822
00:47:13,630 --> 00:47:15,620
Glad to hear that.

823
00:47:19,610 --> 00:47:21,230
Yummy.

824
00:47:21,230 --> 00:47:23,120
Delicious!

825
00:47:23,120 --> 00:47:24,430
Good, good.

826
00:47:24,430 --> 00:47:28,070
It's comforting to see you young people eat so well.

827
00:47:28,070 --> 00:47:30,120
It's delicious, right?

828
00:47:30,120 --> 00:47:32,980
Oto-cchi, you're a genius.

829
00:47:32,980 --> 00:47:34,300
Yummy.

830
00:47:34,300 --> 00:47:35,510
This is too delicious.

831
00:47:35,510 --> 00:47:38,830
If you want a second round, get it yourself.

832
00:47:39,530 --> 00:47:41,750
- Can I?
- Of course.

833
00:47:42,960 --> 00:47:45,150
What's wrong?

834
00:47:47,100 --> 00:47:48,710
My legs...

835
00:47:48,710 --> 00:47:50,940
Don't tell me you have a cramp?

836
00:47:50,940 --> 00:47:52,620
Oh my, what a weakling!

837
00:47:52,620 --> 00:47:54,490
Shut up!

838
00:47:54,490 --> 00:47:56,070
Damn it.

839
00:47:56,070 --> 00:47:59,830
I can't get a second helping like this!

840
00:47:59,830 --> 00:48:02,790
Come on! You've been exaggerating about everything since just now!

841
00:48:02,790 --> 00:48:04,390
Don't laugh, you idiot.

842
00:48:04,390 --> 00:48:06,450
- Okay.
- Stand up!

843
00:48:06,450 --> 00:48:07,710
You can do it!

844
00:48:07,710 --> 00:48:10,210
- Almost...
- It hurts!

845
00:48:10,210 --> 00:48:14,000
- Jeez...
- Try again! You can do it!

846
00:48:19,520 --> 00:48:21,330
My legs...

847
00:48:21,330 --> 00:48:24,560
I must get it... the second helping.

848
00:48:24,560 --> 00:48:26,030
Do I use this?

849
00:48:27,740 --> 00:48:30,750
You don't have to send me back.

850
00:48:30,750 --> 00:48:33,940
Well, I haven't talked about it yet.

851
00:48:33,940 --> 00:48:35,680
What?

852
00:48:35,680 --> 00:48:37,340
About just now...

853
00:48:37,340 --> 00:48:40,210
"Can't I be the one?"

854
00:48:40,210 --> 00:48:42,520
It's okay because I already know it.

855
00:48:42,520 --> 00:48:43,800
What?

856
00:48:44,380 --> 00:48:47,370
You're comparing yourself to that person, aren't you?

857
00:48:48,850 --> 00:48:50,360
How did you know?

858
00:48:50,360 --> 00:48:53,430
Because I know that you care about it.

859
00:48:53,430 --> 00:48:58,280
Even though you'll never win or even be his match.

860
00:48:58,280 --> 00:49:00,240
You don't have to put it so bluntly.

861
00:49:00,240 --> 00:49:02,520
But you said it all yourself, didn't you?

862
00:49:02,520 --> 00:49:04,460
I don't know much about that person.

863
00:49:04,460 --> 00:49:05,940
Huh?

864
00:49:05,940 --> 00:49:08,110
You know him well, right?

865
00:49:08,110 --> 00:49:11,720
No, I don't know about this Domyoji at all.

866
00:49:11,720 --> 00:49:13,740
- What?
- You mentioned him before.

867
00:49:13,740 --> 00:49:18,620
About Domyoji of F4, right?

868
00:49:22,350 --> 00:49:24,020
So, that's what you're referring to.

869
00:49:24,020 --> 00:49:25,890
Well, I do understand.

870
00:49:25,890 --> 00:49:29,300
The way you feel when you compare yourself to a perfect person.

871
00:49:30,090 --> 00:49:32,300
I feel the same, too.

872
00:49:36,540 --> 00:49:37,950
Hey.

873
00:49:38,490 --> 00:49:40,770
Don't tell me...

874
00:49:40,770 --> 00:49:43,750
Yes, I'm talking about Tenma.

875
00:49:43,750 --> 00:49:46,710
He's pushing himself because of me.

876
00:49:49,030 --> 00:49:55,720
My mother was a close friend of his mother, who passed away.

877
00:49:55,720 --> 00:49:58,750
We used to have meals on the last Sunday of every month.

878
00:49:58,750 --> 00:50:03,540
So I still continue to meet him on the last Sunday of every month.

879
00:50:05,400 --> 00:50:10,450
In the past, I used to look forward to meeting him.

880
00:50:10,450 --> 00:50:13,940
I've liked him ever since we met.

881
00:50:13,940 --> 00:50:17,990
I think he's my first love?

882
00:50:18,720 --> 00:50:22,170
I used to laugh naturally in front of him,

883
00:50:22,170 --> 00:50:26,230
but after my father's company went bankrupt,

884
00:50:26,230 --> 00:50:29,710
things were not the same anymore.

885
00:50:29,710 --> 00:50:35,740
"Ah, this dress costs more than a month's salary."

886
00:50:35,740 --> 00:50:38,420
"I wonder how much he paid for the meal."

887
00:50:38,420 --> 00:50:40,420
I feel bad for Tenma.

888
00:50:40,420 --> 00:50:44,160
He's being held down by a promise made by his late mother.

889
00:50:44,160 --> 00:50:51,520
However, my engagement is the only way to save my family.

890
00:50:53,610 --> 00:50:56,920
Sorry to have blabbered so much about myself.

891
00:50:56,920 --> 00:50:58,420
No...

892
00:50:59,090 --> 00:51:00,550
How weird.

893
00:51:00,550 --> 00:51:03,840
I've not told anyone about this before.

894
00:51:05,280 --> 00:51:07,050
If it were me,

895
00:51:07,950 --> 00:51:10,270
I wouldn't have made you think that way.

896
00:51:12,780 --> 00:51:14,120
What?

897
00:51:17,020 --> 00:51:18,960
I won't make you feel troubled.

898
00:51:18,960 --> 00:51:21,140
I won't make you feel bad for me.

899
00:51:22,300 --> 00:51:24,190
Probably.

900
00:51:24,190 --> 00:51:28,280
- What?
- Because you look like a clumsy person.

901
00:51:29,020 --> 00:51:30,620
Don't be ridiculous.

902
00:51:30,620 --> 00:51:35,010
I will become a perfect person! Someone even better than him!

903
00:51:35,010 --> 00:51:39,000
Isn't it okay not to be perfect?

904
00:51:39,950 --> 00:51:40,840
What?

905
00:51:40,840 --> 00:51:45,660
In order to be perfect, you have to put in your best.

906
00:51:45,660 --> 00:51:50,610
But I'm sure you have your own strengths, too.

907
00:51:52,030 --> 00:51:53,540
My own strengths?

908
00:51:53,540 --> 00:51:56,990
You see. When you take muddy vegetables,

909
00:51:56,990 --> 00:52:02,910
wash them and cook them carefully, they will become delicious, right?

910
00:52:02,910 --> 00:52:04,790
It's the same.

911
00:52:17,510 --> 00:52:21,320
You are... also not perfect,

912
00:52:21,320 --> 00:52:23,210
but your food is good.

913
00:52:23,210 --> 00:52:25,670
- What?
- Because...

914
00:52:25,670 --> 00:52:28,820
you can make sausages into octopuses!

915
00:52:31,600 --> 00:52:33,510
What do you mean by that?

916
00:52:43,950 --> 00:52:46,330
Thank you for walking me home.

917
00:52:46,800 --> 00:52:48,430
I say...

918
00:52:49,580 --> 00:52:52,390
You see...

919
00:52:52,910 --> 00:52:55,100
When we were at Domyoji's mansion...

920
00:52:55,100 --> 00:52:56,540
Oh.

921
00:52:56,540 --> 00:52:59,760
You also agree you were too harsh with your words?

922
00:53:00,800 --> 00:53:02,820
In that case, I apologize.

923
00:53:06,900 --> 00:53:09,120
Don't worry about it.

924
00:53:10,070 --> 00:53:12,820
What you said is true.

925
00:53:12,820 --> 00:53:15,500
I'm really living a pathetic life.

926
00:53:17,110 --> 00:53:21,460
Bye. See you tomorrow in school.

927
00:53:23,200 --> 00:53:25,320
Edogawa!

928
00:53:25,320 --> 00:53:27,150
Let's make a promise.

929
00:53:27,950 --> 00:53:32,950
I won't expose your commoner status.

930
00:53:32,950 --> 00:53:36,580
- What?
- You are an exception.

931
00:53:37,650 --> 00:53:39,910
So don't say that you won't have anything to do with me.

932
00:53:39,910 --> 00:53:43,180
Don't say that your life has nothing to do with me.

933
00:53:58,420 --> 00:54:00,380
What a weird fellow.

934
00:54:11,480 --> 00:54:12,570
You are here.

935
00:54:12,570 --> 00:54:14,150
Don't always call me here.

936
00:54:14,150 --> 00:54:15,450
We can see each other in school, right?

937
00:54:15,450 --> 00:54:18,180
I can't say it when the others are around.

938
00:54:18,970 --> 00:54:20,420
My bad.

939
00:54:20,420 --> 00:54:22,770
But it's just like what you said.

940
00:54:22,770 --> 00:54:25,800
I like Oto Edogawa.

941
00:54:25,800 --> 00:54:27,880
But that girl is Tenma Hase's ー

942
00:54:27,880 --> 00:54:31,210
I'll become the most delicious dish of fried vegetables.

943
00:54:32,110 --> 00:54:33,090
Excuse me?

944
00:54:33,090 --> 00:54:35,640
I don't care if she's his fiancée.

945
00:54:35,640 --> 00:54:37,940
I will not lose, for sure!

946
00:54:37,940 --> 00:54:39,980
I'll definitely catch her attention.

947
00:54:39,980 --> 00:54:41,890
I'm sure about it.

948
00:54:41,890 --> 00:54:45,060
I thought you weren't going to waste time on girls?

949
00:54:45,060 --> 00:54:49,350
Who wants a leader who can't have a decent romance?

950
00:54:49,350 --> 00:54:51,210
It's useless for me to say anything.

951
00:54:51,210 --> 00:54:54,220
Yeah, it's decided.

952
00:54:54,800 --> 00:54:57,730
Oto, you seem to be in a good mood this morning.

953
00:54:57,730 --> 00:54:59,040
Really?

954
00:54:59,040 --> 00:55:03,250
Look! The octopuses are smiling.

955
00:55:03,840 --> 00:55:08,760
So, this is how good it feels to not be afraid!

956
00:55:27,320 --> 00:55:30,980
[Oto Edogawa of Class 2-D is a Commoner in Disguise]

957
00:55:34,870 --> 00:55:38,000
I won't let this go.

958
00:55:53,000 --> 00:55:56,460
Why, Kaguragi?

959
00:55:58,700 --> 00:56:01,400
Don't make them a laughing stock!
[She becomes the target of a commoner cull!]

960
00:56:01,910 --> 00:56:03,640
I just can't purge Edogawa from this academy!

961
00:56:03,640 --> 00:56:06,220
Try hurting Oto again, and I'll end you for good.
[Finally, a direct confrontation!]

962
00:56:06,220 --> 00:56:08,660
There are far better people out there for you.
[She decides to end the engagement]

963
00:56:08,660 --> 00:56:12,100
What do you think Domyoji would do?
[That guy from F4 also appears?!]
